-- Qatar May Bid for Christie’s to Help Cultural Status, FT Says
-- B y   D a v i d   A l t a n e r
-- 2010-10-25T00:06:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-25/qatar-may-bid-for-christie-s-to-help-cultural-status-ft-says.html
Qatar may be interested in bidding
for  Christie’s International Plc  auction house, the Financial
Times said, citing an interview with Sheikh Hamad bin Khalifa
al-Thani, the country’s emir.  Controlling Christie’s would help Qatar with its museum as
part of its plans to improve its status as a cultural location
in the Persian Gulf, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 David Altaner  in London at 
